## Business Actors

* Customer
* Seller
* Delivery System
* Payment System
* Reviews
* Items (Products)

## Order Lifecycle & Participating Tables

| Business Process         | Primary Table(s)                     Description                                 |
| ------------------------ | ------------------------ | ----------------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| Customer places an order | `customers`, `orders`    | A customer creates an order.                                                  |
| Order contains products  | `order_items`            | Stores each product purchased within an order.                                |
| Product information      | `products`               | Contains product details for each order item.                                 |
| Seller fulfillment       | `sellers`, `order_items` | Identifies which seller is responsible for each order item.                   |
| Payment processing       | `order_payments`         | Stores payment method, installments, and payment value.                       |
| Order delivery           | `orders`, `geolocation`  | Tracks delivery status and timestamps. Geolocation provides location mapping. |
| Customer review          | `order_reviews`          | Stores ratings and review comments submitted after delivery.                  |

